Open package.json file in your app, find the dependencies section and add this line. The @supabase/supabase-js package will be installed automatically during the build.

"@supabase/supabase-js": "^2.0.0"


Hide

Copy
{
  "name": "your-app",
  "dependencies": {
    "next": "^14.0.0",
    "react": "^18.0.0",
    "@supabase/supabase-js": "^2.0.0"
  }
}

2
Create db.js in the same folder as package.json, paste this code into it, replace 'your_table' with any table name from your Supabase project, and save.

const { createClient } = require(...)...


Hide

Copy
const { createClient } = require('@supabase/supabase-js');

const supabase = createClient(
  process.env.SUPABASE_URL,
  process.env.SUPABASE_API_KEY
);

// Test the connection
supabase
  .from('your_table')
  .select('*')
  .limit(1)
  .then(({ data, error }) => {
    if (error) console.error('Connection error:', error);
    else console.log('Connected:', data);
  });

module.exports = supabase;

3
Push changes to GitHub. Hostinger will redeploy automatically and connect your database.





















